msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:136
#: 861c72a132ce4171876a0080493fe83f
msgid ""
"Prior to the next screen, a compatibility test runs to check whether "
"IOMMU-virtualization is active or not. If the test fails, a window will "
"pop up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:138
#: 2eaa4d010e1e4f3da45dc0f260cc6eed
msgid "|Unsupported hardware detected|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:364
#: f181ab19a4fb4ce191dc02dffd33da40
msgid "Unsupported hardware detected"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:140
#: 95e33942ef87463c9e241c21ef77cc26
msgid ""
"Do not panic. It may simply indicate that IOMMU-virtualization hasn’t "
"been activated in the BIOS or UEFI. Return to the `hardware requirements "
"<#hardware-requirements>`__ section to learn how to activate it. If the "
"setting is not configured correctly, it means that your hardware won’t be"
" able to leverage some Qubes security features, such as a strict "
"isolation of the networking and USB hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:142
#: ff2b4ad63ff54936a1ee1b80874a9ff1
msgid ""
"If the test passes, you will reach the installation summary screen. The "
"installer loads Xen right at the beginning. If you can see the "
"installer’s graphical screen, and you pass the compatibility check that "
"runs immediately afterward, Qubes OS is likely to work on your system!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:144
#: f8331fd7a5204ebf85135f6a3aad817e
msgid ""
"Like Fedora, Qubes OS uses the Anaconda installer. Those that are "
"familiar with RPM-based distributions should feel at home."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:147
#: 2f124dd42abd4b86817fe1ef4033fd36
msgid "Installation summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:152
#: ed24d6ef05664c2d8fc6799492f238d6
msgid ""
"**Did you know?** The Qubes OS installer is completely offline. It "
"doesn’t even load any networking drivers, so there is no possibility of "
"internet-based data leaks or attacks during the installation process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:154
#: 7a68cd5b004d48e1a5dd1fd12816e0e9
msgid ""
"The Installation summary screen allows you to change how the system will "
"be installed and configured, including localization settings. At minimum,"
" you are required to select the storage device on which Qubes OS will be "
"installed."
msgstr ""

