msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:182
#: 58a3b3f917b74c0e8285d37efbe2cb03
msgid ""
"On the software selection tab, you can choose which software to install "
"in Qubes OS. Two options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:184
#: 1b8463228acf491fa183aadf9267e856
msgid ""
"**Debian:** Select this option if you would like to use :doc:`Debian "
"</user/templates/debian/debian>` qubes in addition to the default Fedora "
"qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:186
#: 2065eecc01954bae845ca4693d0a1b07
msgid ""
"**Whonix:** Select this option if you would like to use `Whonix "
"<https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Qubes>`__ qubes. Whonix allows you to use "
"`Tor <https://www.torproject.org/>`__ securely within Qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:190
#: 1b96b9a388ad4cdda9618ccdf3b84b8d
msgid ""
"Whonix lets you route some or all of your network traffic through Tor for"
" greater privacy. Depending on your threat model, you may need to install"
" Whonix templates right away."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:192
#: 08418794fb324c2c9c8a4f6262c2d21b
msgid ""
"Regardless of your choices on this screen, you will always be able to "
"install these and other :doc:`templates </user/templates/templates>` "
"later. If you’re short on disk space, you may wish to deselect these "
"options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:194
#: 36b9bebe25b747a0afce7941bcf1208c
msgid ""
"By default, Qubes OS comes preinstalled with the lightweight Xfce4 "
"desktop environment. Other desktop environments will be available to you "
"after the installation is completed, though they may not be officially "
"supported (see :ref:`advanced topics <advanced-topics>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:196
#: 5ae707af35564ca88f38c672abe92bc2
msgid "Press **Done** to go back to the installation summary screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:199
#: eddd6b24a9894b64868c79ede5ca5732
msgid "Installation destination"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:202
#: a628226188f34f6c86ec409adb6b1b5e
msgid ""
"Under the System section, you must choose the installation destination. "
"Select the storage device on which you would like to install Qubes OS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:206
#: 38f44cea2cae44e9a5caba0327c65404
msgid ""
"**Warning:** Be careful to choose the correct installation target, or you"
" may lose data. We strongly recommended making a full backup before "
"proceeding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:208
#: 8d426860ca1748e8b0064a81df36b59e
msgid ""
"Your installation destination can be an internal or external storage "
"drive, such as an SSD, HDD, or USB drive. The installation destination "
"must have a least 32 GiB of free space available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:212
#: 19988f891fe74fcd9aa246976e3213a1
msgid ""
"**Note:** The installation destination cannot be the same as the "
"installation medium. For example, if you’re installing Qubes OS *from* a "
"USB drive *onto* a USB drive, they must be two distinct USB drives, and "
"they must both be plugged into your computer at the same time. (**Note:**"
" This may not apply to advanced users who partition their devices "
"appropriately.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:214
#: 23d7a45596164f7e84b21137b4219e2c
msgid ""
"Installing an operating system onto a USB drive can be a convenient way "
"to try Qubes. However, USB drives are typically much slower than internal"
" SSDs. We recommend a very fast USB 3.0 drive for decent performance. "
"Please note that a minimum storage of 32 GiB is required. If you want to "
"install Qubes OS onto a USB drive, just select the USB device as the "
"target installation device. Bear in mind that the installation process is"
" likely to take longer than it would on an internal storage device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide-4.1.rst:216
